 of none and of Whom all are in need; He neither begot any nor was He begotten, and none is comparable to Him.芒聙聺","title":"Quran 112:1-4","citations":["quran:112:1-4"],"source_id":"quran:tanzil-simple"},{"block_type":"tafsir_support","domain":"tafsir","text":"Which was revealed in Makkah The Reason for the Revelation of this Surah and its Virtues Imam Ahmad recorded from Ubayy bin Ka`b that the idolators said to the Prophet , \"O Muhammad! Tell us the lineage of your Lord.\" So Allah revealed 脴篓脵聬脴鲁脵聮脵聟脵聬 脴搂脵聞脵聞脵聨脵聭脵聡脵聬 脴搂脵聞脴卤脵聨脵聭脴颅脵聮脵聟脵聨脵聙脵聠脵聬 脴搂脵聞脴卤脵聨脵聭脴颅脵聬脵聤脵聟脵聬 In the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful Similar was recorded by At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Jarir and they added in their narration that he said, 脴搂脵聞脴碌脵聨脵聭脵聟脵聨脴炉脵聫 (As-Samad) is One Who does not give birth, nor was He born, because there is nothing that is born except that it will die, and there is nothing that dies except that","title":"Tafsir Ibn Kathir on Quran 112:1-4","citations":["tafsir:ibn-kathir-en:84552"],"source_id":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en"}]},"evidence":[{"evidence_type":"quran_span","domain":"quran","source_id":"quran:tanzil-simple","canonical_ref":"quran:112:1-4","citation_text":"Quran 112:1-4","payload":{"surah_no":112,"ayah_start":1,"ayah_end":4,"surah_name_en":"al-ikhlas","surah_name_ar":"脴搂脵聞脴楼脴庐脵聞脴搂脴碌","translation_source_id":"quran:towards-understanding-en"}},{"evidence_type":"tafsir_section","domain":"tafsir","source_id":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en","canonical_ref":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en:84552","citation_text":"Tafsir Ibn Kathir on Quran 112:1-4","payload":{"surah_no":112,"ayah_start":1,"ayah_end":4,"coverage_mode":"inferred_from_empty_followers","coverage_confidence":0.95,"anchor_verse_key":"112:1","quran_span_ref":"112:1-4","retrieval_method":null,"matched_terms":[]}}],"conversation":{"followup_ready":true,"anchors":[{"anchor_type":"quran_ref","source_domain":"quran","canonical_ref":"quran:112:1-4","display_text":"Quran 112:1-4"},{"anchor_type":"tafsir_section","source_domain":"tafsir",